    "recap_headline": "Murray State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "ST. CHARLES, Mo. -\nJacob Hustedde\nretired the first 11 batters he faced Saturday to anchor a dominant pitching performance as Murray State defeated Lindenwood 3-1. The victory pulls the Racers (12-7) even in the series and forces a decisive rubber match tomorrow at 10 a.m.\nHustedde earned the win after completing 5 innings of 2-hit ball, allowing just 1 run while racking up 4 punchouts. His efficient outing set the tone for a combined pitching effort that surrendered only 4 hits on the day and limited the Lions to a single run.\nWith his stellar performance today, Hustedde brought his season ERA to 2.50 and has allowed just 2 earned runs over his last 4 starts across 16.2 total innings pitched.\nThe Racers bats didn't produce much noise throughout the game, but Murray State took advantage of 4 walks drawn in the first.\nConnor Chisolm\ngot the Racers on the board with a bases-loaded walk, soon followed by a\nParker Airhart\nsacrifice fly to extend the lead to 2.\nMSU drew 7 walks on the day, led by\nDaylan Pena\nwith 3.\nEach team knocked 4 total hits, with\nConner Cunningham\nhitting a single in his return to the Racers' lineup for his fifth start of the season. Chisolm had the strongest performance at the plate for Murray State, notching 2 hits with 1 double, the only extra-base hit for either team today.\nLindenwood (9-10) scored its lone run on a bases-loaded infield groundout in the sixth.\nReese Oakley\nclosed out the inning strong, holding the Lions to just 1 run after a bases-loaded situation with no outs.\nMurray State added its insurance run in the ninth with\nKristofer Hokenson\nreaching on an error from the pitcher, allowing pinch runner\nJackson McCoy\nto score.\nOakley and\nDylan Zentko\ncombined for 4 shutout innings to close out the win, Zentko earning his fourth save of the season, now leading the MVC in saves. The 2 struck out a combined 6 batters and allowed just 2 hits.\nMurray State and Lindenwood will face off tomorrow in a rubber match at 10 a.m. in St. Charles, Mo.\nFor more information on the Murray State Baseball program, visit GoRacers.com or follow @RacersBaseball on Instagram and X.\nBox Score Notes\nPitching staff struck out 10 batters, the seventh game this season with double-digit strikeouts \u2026 First win this season with four or less hits for Murray State \u2026 Just the third game this season where the Racers didn't steal a base ..\nDylan Zentko\nearned his fourth save of the season, already topping his 2025 season total \u2026 Chisolm's two-hit performance was his fourth multi-hit game of the season."
